The group of detainees broke out of the van while it was travelling from Durban to Krugersdorp on Thursday morning. JOHANNESBURG - Police are searching for an illegal immigrant who escaped along with seven others from a Department of Home Affairs vehicle near the Mooi River Plaza in KwaZulu-Natal.The group of detainees broke out of the van while it was travelling from Durban to Krugersdorp on Thursday morning.The police's Thembeka Mbhele says officers managed to re-arrest seven of the suspects shortly after they fled. One was caught at a Howick area and three others in a Mooi River area. A case of escaping from lawful custody has been opened and will be investigated by Howick detectives. One suspect is still at large. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)